UDRI MAISTORE, KUDE E DJULEVATA RAKIYA
Fixed some bugs, hopefully, and updated to .NET 6.0

First update for the year 2022, poggers. Fixed some stuff, and changed how the playlists/queues work. Added new Feature: Saving Playlists/Queues to a file on the bot host, and uploading it to Discord. They have two formats but I may remove the old one since it was only used during the bot testing period. Also started implementing the Standalone version of the site but I don't think I will work on it soon.

Added new Audio REST Api. I will update it later to add downloading music support, as it now only gives downloaded songs. Also added FfMpeg2.cs which converts the given path to StandardOutput audio.
Added a temporary web socket solution. I have to change it soon, because this solution doesn't support Nginx reverse proxy passthrough.
Added new abuse command which only I can use. Also added some moderator commands like {prefix}ban and {prefix}kick.
Made the GetPlayer method non async, because it doesn't need to be async (smh).
Changed how the FFmpeg client works. Now it has two different methods, one is to directly set the path for FFmpeg, and the other is only for Youtube videos, because of a bug that terminates the connection to the servers and skipping the last 10 seconds of any track that is over 2 minutes. The new method now caches the data in a MemoryStream and then passes it through to the StandardInput of FFmpeg, thus terminating the bug. Also added some arguments for both the FFmpeg instances.
For the HttpClient.cs class I added a custom User Agent, and added a new method called DownloadStream.
Added more information in the basic commands, because many of the player commands didn't send any return text.
For the queue class, I made it return the IPlayableItem which is removed by the RemoveFromQueue method.
I also made the Custom File Format accept file links.

Some generic edits and fixes
Added new Specific Commands and restored old commands.
Added new context menus.

I honestly cannot remember the changes I've done. So I'll just write the most recent one.
ahem.
Fixed the SystemFile.cs class by moving the duration getter up. Also added some new methods in Queue.cs, fixed Spotify Playlist.cs to have a separate method for albums, added a message when the bot fails to get the item 5 times. Added a cancellation token to the PlayTrack method in Player.cs and also added some methods in it. Added search filters in Video.cs (i haven't tested the speed but i think the search might be 2x slower now).
Late night coder, bad.

Huge new update to the bot. Finally added Youtube Live Stream support, although a little slow to find the location (~1.5 seconds). Added custom help command and help command parser (don't ask how much time it took, please I beg you), and overall polished the code in some places.

Changes to CommandsSlash.cs: Fixed some old commands, because they were inefficient and added loop slash command with enum selection, and a move slash command

Thank god I noticed this sooner because I have a feeling it would've been a pain in the arse to fix.
